display="inline"><![CDATA[j]]></fr:tex> is of the form

  <fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>374</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">hodge-theory-i-7.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-i-7.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>7.1</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-i-7</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       {'E_2}^{pq}       = \bigoplus _{\#Q=q} H^p(D_Q,\mathbb {Z})       \Rightarrow  H^{p+q}(U,\mathbb {Z}).     \tag{7.1}     ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

  
  Since each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D_Q]]></fr:tex> is a non-singular projective variety, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{'E_2}^{pq}]]></fr:tex> is endowed with a Hodge structure of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>.
  We set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2^{pq}={'E_2}^{pq}\otimes \mathbb {Z}(-q)]]></fr:tex> (a Hodge structure of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q]]></fr:tex>).
  As an abelian group, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2^{pq}={'E_2}^{pq}]]></fr:tex>;
  it is interesting to consider <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-i-7.1"
href="hodge-theory-i-7.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="7.1" /> as a spectral sequence with initial page <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2^{pq}]]></fr:tex>.
  By <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-i-3"
href="hodge-theory-i-3.xml"
number="3" />, we should expect for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d_2\colon  E_2^{pq}\to  E_2^{p+2,q-1}]]></fr:tex> to be a morphism of Hodge structures.
  We prove this by thinking of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d_2]]></fr:tex> as a Gysin morphism.
  Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_3^{pq}]]></fr:tex> is endowed with a Hodge structure of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q]]></fr:tex>.
  By <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-i-3"
href="hodge-theory-i-3.xml"
number="3" />, we expect, <fr:em>modulo torsion</fr:em>, for the spectral sequence (<fr:em>[Trans.] The original refers to (6.4) instead of (6.2), but this seems to be a typo.</fr:em>) <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-i-6.2"
href="hodge-theory-i-6.2.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="6.2" /> to degenerate at the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_3]]></fr:tex> page (i.e. <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_3=E_\infty ]]></fr:tex>), and for the vanishing of the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d_r]]></fr:tex> (for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r\geq 3]]></fr:tex>) to be an application of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-i-5"
href="hodge-theory-i-5.xml"
number="5" />.
  This programme was successfully completed in <fr:link
type="local"
href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.xml"
addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2"
title="Hodge Theory II › Hodge theory of non-singular algebraic varieties › Mixed Hodge theory">[Hodge Theory II, 3.2]</fr:link>.
  There, we <fr:em>define</fr:em> the weight filtration of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H^\bullet (U,\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex> as the abutment of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-i-7.1"
href="hodge-theory-i-7.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="7.1" />, up to renumbering <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-i-6.3"
href="hodge-theory-i-6.3.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="6.3" />.</fr:p><fr:p>In fact, to endow the cohomology groups <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H^\bullet ]]></fr:tex> with a mixed Hodge structure, the key point has always been, up until now, to find a spectral sequence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> abutting to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H^\bullet ]]></fr:tex> such that the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[l]]></fr:tex>-adic analogue of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2^{pq}]]></fr:tex> be conjecturally pure (of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q]]></fr:tex>);
  <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2^{pq}]]></fr:tex> should then carry a natural Hodge structure (of weight <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q]]></fr:tex>), and the filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> is then the abutment of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>